comments.description: Check if ``val`` is an instance of the ``Error`` prototype. Because error objects may originate from different globals, comparing the prototype of the left hand side with the prototype property from the right hand side, which is what ``instanceof`` does, will not work. If the LHS and RHS come from different globals, this check will always fail because the two objects will not have the same identity. Therefore it is not safe to use ``instanceof`` in any multi-global situation, e.g. in content across multiple ``Window`` objects or anywhere in chrome scope. This function also contains a special check if ``val`` is an XPCOM ``nsIException`` because they are special snowflakes and may indeed cause Firefox to crash if used with ``instanceof``.
